<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-11-11T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-11-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="639" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d639">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">881.156/50: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Diplomatic Agent and Consul General at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Denning</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-11T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November 11,
                                        1922—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>22. Your November 9, 7 p.m.</p>
                        <p>American Embassy Paris telegraphs that French Government attributes
                            postponement to financial reasons. Report local developments, and advise
                            by cable of any requests that you may receive looking to your joining in
                            protest by Diplomatic Corps against legality of concession.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>